quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  17,1,"Highly Exalted is the One Who took His servant on a journey by night from the Inviolable Mosque{1}to the Farthest Mosque{2}, whose precincts We<a class=",footnotes:1:<i>Al-masjid Al-Harām</i> in Makkah.,footnotes:2:<i>Al-masjid Al-Aqsa</i> in Jerusalem<i>.</i>,footnotes:3:A grammatical shift from 3<sup>rd</sup> to person 1 to person 1<sup>st</sup> person. person.
  17,2,"And We brought Moses the Scripture and made it guidance for the Children of Israel<span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Abu Amr read it as: “…for the Children of Israel, that they may take none for trustee other than Me.</span>
  17,3,"(O) offspring of those We carried with Noah; indeed, he was a constantly thankful servant.”"
  17,4,"And We decreed for the Children of Israel in the Scripture: “You will most surely corrupt in the land twice, and you will most surely rise to a great height."
  17,5,"Then when the promise of the first of the two times came true, We sent against youpl servants of Ours possessing intense force, and they ransacked the homes, and it was a promise fulfilled.”"
  17,6,"Then We gave youpl back your turn against them and supplied you with wealth and offspring and made you more numerous."
  17,7,"If you excel in doing good, you excel in doing good to your own benefit; and if you do evil, you do so against yourselves. Then when the promise of the second time comes true, <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer, Shu’ba, Hamza and Khalaf read it as: “…He will defile…” Al-Kesa’i read it as: “…We will defile…”</span>